# .easignore — controls what EAS Build uploads to the cloud builder.
#
# IMPORTANT: this lives at the GIT ROOT on purpose. The Expo app is in size-matters/,
# but the git repository root is HERE, and EAS archives the project from the git root —
# so a size-matters/.easignore is NOT applied (its paths resolve against the repo root
# and never match the subfolder). That mismatch was uploading the entire repo
# (node_modules + 166 MB of dev screenshots + sibling folders) ≈ 491 MB every build.
# Paths below are repo-root-relative.
#
# When a .easignore is present, EAS uses it INSTEAD of .gitignore, so this is a full
# superset of the excludes that matter.

# === Everything in this repo EXCEPT the Expo app (size-matters/) ===
/Assets/
/Revenue Cat/
/Size Matters RevenueCat/
/SM Content/
/proxy/
/resize-demo/
/push-to-github.sh

# === App dependencies (reinstalled on the build server from bun.lock) ===
node_modules/

# === Secrets / credentials (provided via EAS env vars; never upload) ===
.env
.env.*
*.env
.env*.local
!.env.example
*.p8
*.p12
*.key
*.jks
*.pem
*.mobileprovision

# === Generated native projects (EAS runs prebuild) ===
size-matters/ios/
size-matters/android/

# === Expo / Metro / build caches ===
.expo/
dist/
web-build/
expo-env.d.ts
.metro-health-check*
*.tsbuildinfo
*.orig.*
expo.log

# === Heavy web/dev screenshots (~166 MB) — keep ONLY the FishTapGame sound effects ===
size-matters/public/*
!size-matters/public/*.mp3

# === logs & OS cruft ===
npm-debug.*
yarn-debug.*
yarn-error.*
.DS_Store
*.DS_Store
